headline: S&P Global Mobility:  U.S. auto sales showing signs of progress
summary: On an unadjusted volume level, S&P Global Mobility projects November US light vehicle sales to reach 1.31 million units, growth of 6% from the year ago level. This would translate to a seasonally adjusted rate (SAAR) of 15.9 million units, on trend with the 16.0 million unit mark realized in October.

headline: CARFAX: Millions of Cars Are Alarmingly Behind on Maintenance
summary: As millions of people hit the road this holiday season, CARFAX estimates almost 20 percent of cars on the road are behind on oil changes, and nearly 30 percent are behind on tire rotations. CARFAX estimates more than 30 million vehicles are behind on both services.
